The paper deals with the problem of designing the topology of a sensor network to maximize the rate of convergence of average consensus, taking into account communication costs and constraints on resources such as power and data rate. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Computer Science dealing with Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
